      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "EFFORTLESSLY (7) came from the clouds to arrive just in time to get the verdict and shed her maiden tag here last time. Keeps Pike and will appreciate stretching the extra 100m. Expecting her to go on with it. ROSENTREA (3) got off the mark in determined fashion first-up here and has been solid since. Strips rock-hard fit and has enough early dash to offset the sticky draw if CJP is inclined. Can give a sight. JOYOH (5) possesses a nice turn of foot and if Parnham has her close when they sprint, she can put them away. Expecting her to be a couple pairs closer than EFFORTLESSLY which is a big plus. BONDI STAR (6) wasn't far away first-up despite finishing out of the placings. Strips fitter and will find this a bit easier dropping back from a CL3. Not hopeless. KAT FIVE (8) proved versatile with her speed last time when making her run from a long way back. Has her share of ability and is worth respecting.",
